# Kubernetes Day 2 Notes

# Kubernetes Architecture

Kubernetes architecture defines how different components work together to deploy and manage containerized applications.

A Kubernetes Cluster consists of:

* Control Plane
* Worker Nodes

---

# What is a Kubernetes Cluster?

A Kubernetes Cluster is a collection of multiple servers (nodes) working together to run applications.

It is **NOT another server**.

Think of it as a team of servers.

```text
Kubernetes Cluster

├── Control Plane
└── Worker Nodes
```

---

# Real-Life Analogy

School

↓

Principal

↓

Teachers

↓

